{
  "stem": "17426.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 109.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course on every holiday, we received-- each holiday in-- during Yom Kippur, Rosh Hashana, and during Passover-- fresh clothes to go to shul.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had his own seat for his lifetime at the shul.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was always given mitzvot and-- in the shul.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he lived a life that one can say was completely devoted to his family, more so than to his work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His family was so precious to him that when he traveled somewhere, and he always brought something back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "For example, oranges in those days were a luxury.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And just the oranges that we have-- had in Poland were usually coming from Palestine, from Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there were these so-called bloody oranges, with red inside.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And if he would buy some oranges somewhere, which we couldn't buy in Dobra, he would bring them to us and share them with us, always.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he always would bring something for his children, whether it is a small gift-- usually small gifts, because we were not that affluent.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I used to love to drive with him, as he was visiting the German Junkers that had large [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] farms around our area.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, he traded with them, and he was usually going to visit them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he would take me into these so-called [POLISH] [POLISH], which means the very upscale houses and-- and seats of these Junkers and introduce me to them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would spend some time with their children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would take me out in the gardens.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I would pick cherries, and we would pick apples, and we would pick pears.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I would usually get some to take home with me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was fun times for me as I was growing up.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
